reviewText: I picked this up cheap just to see DeForest Kelley in his pre-Star Trek days, and for that purpose, it was moderately successful. Unfortunately the movie itself is just wall-to-wall clap-trap about the importance of God in your life. The message was not for me, but De Kelley will always be a favorite of mine.
see deforest kelley in his early days in the movies playing a doctor .and its not doctor McCoy. Its a much earlier time and its a movie with a a true feeling.
It is Christian film, it portrays the Gospel and the New Testament.  DeForest Kelly has a strong, quiet role.  Anyone who is a fan of DeForest Kelley must have this movie.
